This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with zero-shot learning for visual samples. It also involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a novel method for zero-shot learning. Additionally, it involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with the generation of unseen features from semantic descriptions. The paper also involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with semantic descriptions and their corresponding visual features. Finally, it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with the generation of visual features from semantic descriptions.
